Text.Value: Got any goods for sale?
Well! Look what the cat dragged in. Haven't seen you since you cleared up me ol' noggin in the Underdark.
Not as chipper as you, it seems.
How ya been?
No time to waste dragging my feet. Got to make up for the time I wasted while my brains were inside out.
Only the finest. And to thank you for your good help, I'll take a lot off the top - just for you.
Fled in the night and haven't seen her ugly face since. For the best; she was cruising for a lesson after what she did.
Derryth's coming back soon. Stepped out, she has. I'll keep an eye out.
Thanks to you. If I hadn't run into you in that mushroom field, my old bag Derryth would've had me at her beck and call to this day.
Leave.
To quote you, I can't complain. I hear this and that about Absolutists in the city and someone running around on a murder spree, but I haven't had any trouble.
I didn't think so. So don't you be judging me.
Can't complain.
Welcome back, mate.
It's Bonecloak's! I'm Baelen. Hello, nice to meet you.
Nor should you. 'Tis a beautiful day to be alive.
Glad to see you up and about.
Go on, Baelen, get on with it then.
Good, but I need supplies. Got anything to trade?
Have a good long gander, now.
We sell all sorts of ingredients and goods.
If I'm lucky, they'll go for Derryth next. Heh!
How are things in the city?
Don't you be judging me. Sure you made it to the city with curtsies and cajoles, is that right?
I wouldn't have healed you if I knew you were a violent man.
I'd like to trade.
I've got to finish this, now. Bye!

EditorData.NodeContext: whispered, maybe hand next to mouth like telling a secret. friendly

Text.Value: Where is Derryth?

Synopsis: If Baelen survives the Underdark, you can talk to him in the Bonecloak Apothecary upon your arrival in LOW. He is either running the shop after harrying his wife away for the last time, or his mind is almost completely gone and he is effectively Derryth's servant.
